Text: Here are the documents on the Marquez family.

It's extremely helpful when the people you're digging
into self-report... Much appreciated, Gamma.
Heheh... It's nothing really!
Well, it reduces my workload.
Seriously, Zeta?!
Zeta...I see you haven't changed.

...It appears Marquess Marquez often makes outings to
Oriana Kingdom for the purpose of purchasing artwork.

Yes, the Marquez family is not only an aristocratic
family of dark knights, but also one which made
their fortune in trading fine art.

In other words, they have more financial resources
than other marquesses. I wonder if that's why they've
been able to hide this matter from the public.

The relationships between aristocrats are so flimsy
that if there's even the slightest opportunity, they'll
immediately try to oust each other.

But I haven't seen any such movements. I guess that
means the Cult has a handle on things in this instance.

Do we know where the Marquez family imports and sells
art from Oriana Kingdom?

Under the guise of transporting artwork, the Marquess
could be using their transport route to escort the
possessed to their destination.

It mainly connects to Midgar Kingdom and the Sacred
Land of Lindwurm—Oh!

If Lindwurm is an option, it's a convenient route for
bringing in the possessed.

Even the hideout we previously raided was a place to
bring in the possessed.

It's a worthy route to keep an eye on. Guess all
that's left is the response to the Templars!

Just as we're predicting the movement of the Cult,
they must be preparing to raid the transport of the
possessed.

In that case, it seems convenient...to hit them all
together.

And to do so, we, the Shadow Garden, can intervene at
the ideal moment of the Templars' raid.
Lady Alpha!

The Templars now know we exist. There's no need to
play tricks. We can hit them head-on!

Personally, I think that'll be the quickest and most
effective solution.
Um, so long as I can play rough, I'm fine with that!

The more test subjects in actual battle, the
better... Heheh.
...I'll uncover the convoy route.

From there, we can pick the ideal location for the
raid, consider the Templars' movements, and
narrow down our potential options!

Gamma, could you come up with a detailed strategy?
If you're busy, I'll leave it to someone else in the
Seven Shadows...
Leave it to me! I, Gamma, promise to handle... Aagh?!
You two support Gamma.
Very well! Understood!
...I'll do my best!

...We've found a human possessed. We plan on rescuing
her as soon as we have a plan in place.
Oh? A human possessed...
Yes. Cases of human possession...are rare.

(I don't know how rare it is, but if Alpha says so,
well, I guess it is. I've personally only seen it
happen with my sister.)

(But the fact is they do exist, so of course, there
must be others.)

(I'm glad to see the girls are not only willing to
play along with my whole shadowbroker scenario,
but they've also realized the inadequacy of the
setting they've come up with.)

(It's a bit biased to create a setting where only
elves and therianthrope girls are possessed.)

(For starters, there's something absurd about the
whole "girls-only" setting. I get they want to host
girls' nights out and all that, but...)
So, Cid, there's something I'd like to ask you.
Ask me? What is it?

Yes...your method of curing possessed humans.
Humans are fundamentally different from elves
and therianthropes, aren't they?
(...Hold on. They're "fundamentally" different?!)

(Well, sure, their magic circuits are made
differently, but...)

(For that matter, even amongst elves, there are,
of course, slight differences in each individual's
circuitry...)

I am sure you can cure human possession just
as easily as you can cure possession in elves
or therianthropes.

But the rest of us are still inexperienced, so we may
not be able to do it as well as you—

You sure about that? If you give it a try, it might
be easier than you think.

I...hope that's the case...! Still, if there's something
I can learn, I'd like to know about it in advance.

(Now that I think about it, I came up with a cure
after a month of trying different things on Alpha
when she was a mound of flesh... That's how I
acquired the skill.)

(It's only natural that there's a difference in
perception between Alpha and me. I acquired
a universal cure technique applicable to any
species through trial and error.)

(I see. Alpha's move is to beg to be taught by
setting up a scenario that does not conflict with
that fact. She's come a long way.)

...For human possession, I'm assuming it's important
to do the "stretches" you showed your sister.
Hm?

...That's right. But that alone is not enough.
Stretching itself only makes the body more
flexible. It's no different than a massage.
Really?! Then...
It's up to you to find your own answers from there.

More than merely learning from my words, you can
acquire the truth through your own experience using
my words as a clue. There's a world of difference
between the two, even if you gain the same knowledge.
Cid...!

...Very well. I will rely on your words and figure it
out on my own!
(Phew! Close call...!)

(I can't just come out and say that the stretching
was an experiment...an excuse to gain control
over the magic in my sister's body!)

(I've got to be very careful about how I lay out each
and every scenario since I'm having them follow me
on my shadowbroker movement. Otherwise, I would
be doing the girls a disservice.)
Looks like we've reached a new phase.
Yes...but we can't afford to stop here.

That's right. We are the Shadow Garden. We lurk
 in the darkness and hunt down shadows...
That's why we exist—
(Oh... I kinda like the way this is going.)

(I feel that buzz of excitement akin to the re-launch
of a comic or film series that was just starting to
get stale, where you're starting all over with
various new scenarios.)

Alpha...don't take your eyes off the ball on this
one.

There's a high chance...that human possessions, which
are scarce in number, hold some secret they seek—

*gasp* I knew you would surmise the same thing!
You grasp the situation completely without me
having to tell you anything—

(A thought-provoking phrase in the face of newly
arising circumstances...)

(Heh...This is the fundamental of a shadowbroker,
the move I must constantly strive toward!)

Very well... I'll get to work on strategizing with an
open mind. In the name of you, Shadow, and the
Shadow Garden!

(Boy does Alpha have a knack for improvising.
She really excels at everything she does!)
